!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

responsible /rɪˈspɒnsəbəl/

1. ADJ If someone or something is responsible for a particular event or situation, they are the cause of it or they can be blamed for it. 负有责任的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： He still felt responsible for her death. 他依然觉得对她的死负有责任。 

2. ADJ If you are responsible for something, it is your job or duty to deal with it and make decisions relating to it. 负责的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： ...the cabinet member responsible for the environment. …负责环境的内阁成员。 

3. ADJ If you are responsible to a person or group, they have authority over you and you have to report to them about what you do. 向…汇报的 [v-link ADJ 'to' n] 

例： I'm responsible to my board of directors. 我向我的董事会汇报。 

4. ADJ Responsible people behave properly and sensibly, without needing to be supervised. 有责任心的 

例： He feels that the media should be more responsible in what they report. 他觉得媒体应该对他们的报道更负责些。 

5. responsibly ADV 有责任心地 [ADV with v] 

例： He urged everyone to act responsibly. 他力劝每一个人做事要负责。 

6. ADJ Responsible jobs involve making important decisions or carrying out important tasks. 责任重大的 [ADJ n] 

例： You are too young for such a responsible position. 对于这样一个责任重大的职位，你太年轻了。

</div>

